tiate for yourself own your own success i wish i could tell that to my daughter but its not that simple sheryl sandberg work success women so theres no such thing as worklife balance theres work and theres life and theres no balance sheryl sandberg life work balance if more women are in leadership roles well stop assuming they shouldnt be sheryl sandberg leadership women stop if you ask men why they did a good job theyll say im awesome obviously why are you even asking if you ask women why they did a good job what theyll say is someone helped them they got lucky they worked really hard sheryl sandberg women good job i feel really grateful to the people who encouraged me and helped me develop nobody can succeed on their own sheryl sandberg grateful people me women attribute their success to working hard luck and help from other people men will attribute that  whatever success they have that same success  to their own core skills sheryl sandberg success women men what about the rat race in the first place is it worthwhile or are you just buying into someone elses definition of success only you can decide that and youll have to decide it over and over and over but if you think its a rat race before you drop out take a deep breath maybe you picked the wrong job try again and then try again sheryl sandberg success deep job i really think we need more women to lean into their careers and to be really dedicated to staying in the work force sheryl sandberg work women think i have never worked for a woman and i have never worked with a lot of women sheryl sandberg women woman never i would be better at my job if i were technical sheryl sandberg job better would its easy to dislike the few senior women out there what if women were half the positions in power it would be harder to dislike all of them sheryl sandberg women power easy when youre more valuable the people around you will do more to make it work sheryl sandberg work people you i go around the room and ask people what do you think sheryl sandberg people think you for any of us in this room today lets start out by admitting were lucky we dont live in the world our mothers lived in our grandmothers lived in where career choices for women were so limited sheryl sandberg women today choices women are not making it to the top a hundred and ninety heads of state nine are women of all the people in parliament in the world thirteen per cent are women in the corporate sector women at the top  clevel jobs board seats  tops out at fifteen sixteen per cent sheryl sandberg women world people most people assume that women are responsible for households and child care most couples operate that way  not all that fundamental assumption holds women back sheryl sandberg women child care the no  impediment to women succeeding in the workforce is now in the home sheryl sandberg home women now weve got to get women to sit at the table sheryl sandberg women sit table i have a five yearold son and a three yearold daughter i want my son to have a choice to contribute fully in the workforce or at home and i want my daughter to have the choice to not just succeed but to be liked for her accomplishments sheryl sandberg home daughter son what i tell everyone and i really do for myself is i have a longrun dream which is i want to work on stuff that i think matters sheryl sandberg work myself dream but i really believe that when you give people authentic identity which is what facebook does and you can be your real self and connect with real people online things will change sheryl sandberg change self believe in fact my new years resolution every year and im jewish so i get two new years a year is to meditate and i fail every time sheryl sandberg time new two we call our little girls bossy go to a playground little girls get called bossy all the time  a word thats almost never used for boys  and that leads directly to the problems women face in the workforce sheryl sandberg time women problems share this pa